from folium import plugins
# instantiate a feature group for the airports in the dataframe
Airports = folium.map.FeatureGroup()

# loop through the airports and add each to the location to the feature group
for lat, lng, in zip(df_Airports.latitude, df_Airports.longitude):
    Airports.add_child(
        folium.CircleMarker(
            [lat, lng],
            radius=5, # define how big you want the circle markers to be
            color='yellow',
            fill=True,
            fill_color='blue',
            fill_opacity=0.6
        )
    )

# add incidents to map
sweden_map.add_child(Airports)

In [37]:
# AIRPORT GROUPED ACCORDING TO COUNTIES AND NAME
from folium.plugins import MeasureControl # measurement plugins in folium
sweden_map = folium.Map(location = [latitude, longitude], zoom_start = 4)

# instantiate a mark cluster object for the airports in the dataframe
Airports = plugins.MarkerCluster().add_to(sweden_map)
# Adds tool to the top right
sweden_map.add_child(MeasureControl())

# circle marker for airports with charging stations 
folium.CircleMarker([57.7747, 11.8704], 
                   radius=30,
                    popup='Charger',
                   color='red',
                  ).add_to(Airports)
 
folium.CircleMarker([58.31809997558584, 12.3450002670228809],
                   radius=30,
                    popup='Charger',
                   color='red',
                  ).add_to(Airports)

folium.CircleMarker([57.69559860229492, 12.84280014038086],
                   radius=30,
                    popup='Charger',
                   color='red',
                  ).add_to(Airports)

# loop through the dataframe and add each data point to the mark cluster
for lat, lng, label in zip(df_Airports.latitude, df_Airports.longitude, df_Airports.type):
    folium.Marker(
        location=[lat, lng],
        icon=None,
        popup=label,
    ).add_to(Airports)

# display map
sweden_map

# AIRPORT WITHOUT GROUPING BUT DISPLAY NAME AND TYPE(AFTER ZOOMING CLOSELY)
Airports = folium.map.FeatureGroup()
# loop through the airports and add each location to the feature group
for lat, lng, in zip(df_Airports.latitude, df_Airports.longitude):
    Airports.add_child(
        folium.CircleMarker(
            [lat, lng],
            radius=2, # define how big you want the circle markers to be
            color='yellow',
            fill=True,
            fill_color='blue',
            fill_opacity=0.6
        )
    )

#circle marker for airports with charging stations  
folium.CircleMarker([57.7747, 11.8704],
                   radius=30,
                    popup='Charger',
                   color='red',
                  ).add_to(Airports)
 
folium.CircleMarker([58.31809997558584, 12.3450002670228809],
                   radius=30,
                    popup='Charger',
                   color='red',
                  ).add_to(Airports)

folium.CircleMarker([57.69559860229492, 12.84280014038086],
                   radius=30,
                    popup='Charger',
                   color='red',
                  ).add_to(Airports)

# add pop-up text to each marker on the map
latitudes = list(df_Airports.latitude)
longitudes = list(df_Airports.longitude)
labels = list(df_Airports.name)


for lat, lng, label in zip(latitudes, longitudes, labels):
    folium.Marker([lat, lng], popup=label).add_to(sweden_map) 
    
# add incidents to map
sweden_map.add_child(Airports)
